-- French June current account deficit widens on BNP fine
-- 
-- Tue Aug 12, 2014 03:22AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, Aug 12 (Reuters) - France's current account deficit widened in June to 7.4 billion euros ($9.9 billion) due to bank BNP Paribas <BNPPA.PA> having to pay a large fine in a U.S. sanctions busting affair, the Bank of France said on Tuesday.

